Professional Interest Groups
The American Diabetes Association's Professional Interest Groups provide a forum for the exchange of information in specific areas of diabetes research and care. With more than 13,000 members, these groups contribute to the Association in a variety of valuable ways with members serving on policy-making committees; writing technical reviews, position statements, and other publications; and acting as liaisons to peer organizations.

Become a member to take full advantage of these professional networking opportunities in your specialty.

Visit these interest group webpages for the latest resources and information:
